<i>Into the clouds in the sky, gradually fading away</i>

8
00:00:38,724 --> 00:00:42,994
KOBAYASHI ASAKO / YOSHIMOTO NAHOKO
KIYOBUMI KANEKO / UNO SHOHEI
Sora ni ukabu kumo no naka ni sukoshi zutsu kiete yuku
<i>Into the clouds in the sky, gradually fading away</i>

9
00:00:42,994 --> 00:00:45,199
Sora ni ukabu kumo no naka ni sukoshi zutsu kiete yuku
<i>Into the clouds in the sky, gradually fading away</i>

10
00:00:45,832 --> 00:00:46,457
Toku takai sora no naka de te o nobasu shiroi kumo
<i>From up above in the sky white clouds reach down</i>

11
00:00:46,457 --> 00:00:50,400
HAJIZUME RYU / HARADA CHIEKO / SUZUKI TATSUYA
Toku takai sora no naka de te o nobasu shiroi kumo
<i>From up above in the sky white clouds reach down</i>

12
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:54,799
Toku takai sora no naka de te o nobasu shiroi kumo
<i>From up above in the sky white clouds reach down</i>

13
00:00:55,853 --> 00:00:57,113
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

14
00:00:57,113 --> 00:01:02,379
<i>At the end of the day, when people are rushing home...</i>
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

15
00:01:02,379 --> 00:01:05,121
<i>...That's when my day starts.</i>
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

16
00:01:06,808 --> 00:01:15,980
Zutto mukashi no koto no yoda ne
<i>Always seems like a thing of the past</i>

17
00:01:16,808 --> 00:01:21,535
Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
<i>Clouds passing over a flowing river</i>

18
00:01:21,535 --> 00:01:26,675
<i>My business hours start from midnight to 7 am.</i>
Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
<i>Clouds passing over a flowing river</i>

19
00:01:27,198 --> 00:01:31,728
<i>People call my restaurant 'the late night diner.'</i>

20
00:01:32,528 --> 00:01:34,838
[MESHIYA]

21
00:01:34,838 --> 00:01:39,478
<i>Do customers come? You ask...
There's quite a number who do.</i>

22
00:01:41,960 --> 00:01:50,378
<i>Wabi-Sabi Subs presents:</i>
<b>SHINYA SHOKUDO Season 3</b>
"Late Night Diner"
EP 5: "BEAN VERMICELLI SALAD..."

23
00:01:52,963 --> 00:01:56,258
<i>It's been raining since nightfall.</i>

24
00:01:56,258 --> 00:02:02,918
<i>I wonder if it's better to carry an umbrella
or maybe better off without it... in a harusame*...</i>
(*"Spring rain", also "bean starch vermicelli noodles")

25
00:02:02,918 --> 00:02:05,298
- This is the place.
- Oh, okay...

26
00:02:05,718 --> 00:02:07,608
Good evening.

27
00:02:07,608 --> 00:02:09,268
Welcome.

28
00:02:09,268 --> 00:02:10,518
Is it still raining?

29
00:02:10,518 --> 00:02:12,928
Yeah. We didn't bring umbrellas though.

30
00:02:12,928 --> 00:02:14,188
Beer for now please.

31
00:02:14,188 --> 00:02:15,308
Sure thing.

32
00:02:15,608 --> 00:02:17,418
- Is it okay?
- Yeah.

33
00:02:17,568 --> 00:02:20,428
If you say what you want to eat,
most of the time, this shop can make it so...

34
00:02:20,428 --> 00:02:21,978
...ask away.
- Really?

35
00:02:21,978 --> 00:02:24,568
Wonder what to order...

36
00:02:24,568 --> 00:02:27,158
Anyway, I was shocked.

37
00:02:27,158 --> 00:02:30,008
Yama-chan's head had become like that...

38
00:02:30,008 --> 00:02:33,948
- To think I had a crush on him a long time ago.
- 'Cause Yama-chan seemed to had it tough.

39
00:02:33,948 --> 00:02:36,228
With all the restructuring and the divorce...

40
00:02:36,228 --> 00:02:40,488
I see, so with all the troubles,
he lost all of his hair.

41
00:02:40,488 --> 00:02:41,808
Here you go.

42
00:02:42,198 --> 00:02:46,468
Master, this is my elementary school classmate, Sayuri.
She's a teacher now in our alma mater.

43
00:02:46,468 --> 00:02:47,618
Hello.

44
00:02:47,618 --> 00:02:48,768
Did you have an class reunion today?

45
00:02:48,768 --> 00:02:51,158
No. Our reunion is at the
end of the month but...

46
00:02:51,158 --> 00:02:54,978
We both became the organizers
and we just came from the meeting today.

47
00:02:54,978 --> 00:02:57,618
Our class buried a time capsule
at the time of our graduation...

48
00:02:57,618 --> 00:03:00,698
And we're gonna dig it up after 25 years
so the preparations is already getting hard.

49
00:03:00,698 --> 00:03:03,828
Really... 25 years ....

50
00:03:03,828 --> 00:03:04,988
Yeah.

51
00:03:04,988 --> 00:03:09,468
Speaking of time capsules,
the one that's famous is...

52
00:03:09,468 --> 00:03:12,798
...the one that's buried in Osaka Castle Park
during the Expo 1970 in Osaka.

53
00:03:12,798 --> 00:03:16,938
They'll dig it up in the year 6970,
a whopping 5000 years after.

54
00:03:18,118 --> 00:03:19,978
When I was also in elementary school...

55
00:03:19,978 --> 00:03:21,418
...our class buried one, too.

56
00:03:21,418 --> 00:03:22,758
So what happened to it?

57
00:03:22,758 --> 00:03:26,828
When we dug it up after 10 years,
there was water inside, and got stained...

58
00:03:26,828 --> 00:03:29,488
The letters were indecipherable,
we couldn't read them anymore.

59
00:03:29,488 --> 00:03:31,888
Really, can such a thing happen?

60
00:03:31,888 --> 00:03:35,728
The capsule's lid wasn't closed properly.

61
00:03:35,728 --> 00:03:38,288
It's good that yours is going well...

62
00:03:38,288 --> 00:03:41,658
As someone from the same generation,
I wish you good luck.

63
00:03:41,658 --> 00:03:43,468
Same generation!?

64
00:03:44,588 --> 00:03:46,278
What? You got a problem with that?

65
00:03:46,278 --> 00:03:48,618
You graduated 25 years ago so...

66
00:03:48,618 --> 00:03:50,718
Hey! Don't calculate it!

67
00:03:52,418 --> 00:03:54,738
Hey Sayuri. Have you decided what to eat?

68
00:03:55,148 --> 00:03:58,058
Yeah. Vermicelli salad.

69
00:04:14,241 --> 00:04:16,498
Here, thanks for waiting.

70
00:04:16,498 --> 00:04:19,168
I'm digging in.

71
00:04:27,928 --> 00:04:30,558
- Delicious!
- Yeah.

72
00:04:30,558 --> 00:04:33,628
Hey, speaking of vermicelli salad,
it's Shigacchi, right?

73
00:04:33,628 --> 00:04:37,168
Didn't you use to get food
from someone else at lunchtime?

74
00:04:38,048 --> 00:04:40,768
You remember the strange things, don't you?

75
00:04:40,768 --> 00:04:45,058
I liked Yama-chan and
kept following him around.

76
00:04:45,308 --> 00:04:47,728
Oh, Sayuri, who was your crush back then?

77
00:04:51,978 --> 00:04:54,158
Tell me~.

78
00:04:54,158 --> 00:04:56,168
Shigacchi.

79
00:04:56,418 --> 00:04:58,178
You liked him?

80
00:05:00,988 --> 00:05:06,058
The truth is I hated vermicelli salad.

81
00:05:06,458 --> 00:05:09,148
But since I really liked Shiga-kun...

82
00:05:10,434 --> 00:05:12,868
...I thought, I'll come to like it, too, I guess.

83
00:05:12,868 --> 00:05:16,898
When I ate it every day...
I came to love it before I realized it.

84
00:05:17,048 --> 00:05:22,418
I see. Then, it would be great
if Shigacchi comes to the reunion, huh.

85
00:05:22,700 --> 00:05:23,778
Yeah.

86
00:05:25,938 --> 00:05:27,118
Have you reached it?

87
00:05:27,118 --> 00:05:30,758
I don't know. Ah~ I can't anymore. Take over.

88
00:05:30,758 --> 00:05:33,198
- Ah~ so dirty...
- It's okay... You can do it...

89
00:05:33,598 --> 00:05:36,128
We'll be waiting, do your best.

90
00:05:38,048 --> 00:05:41,992
Say, Yama-chan. Didn't you see Sayuri?

91
00:05:42,125 --> 00:05:45,378
Huh? I haven't seen her...
she's didn't come?

92
00:05:45,378 --> 00:05:48,608
I can't even contact her phone.

93
00:05:48,758 --> 00:05:50,998
It's a mystery, isn't it?

94
00:05:50,998 --> 00:05:52,728
It is a wonder...

95
00:05:59,304 --> 00:06:02,258
Are you perhaps Tajima?

96
00:06:08,938 --> 00:06:10,698
Shigacchi?

97
00:06:13,538 --> 00:06:15,368
Oh, we found it!

98
00:06:18,228 --> 00:06:23,168
Oh, um... I've completely mistaken you
for Miho-san's husband. I'm so sorry.

99
00:06:23,778 --> 00:06:26,458
I'm Shiga, her elementary school classmate.

100
00:06:26,458 --> 00:06:28,968
Ah. The rumored Shigacchi-san...

101
00:06:28,968 --> 00:06:31,508
- What?
- Uh, so here's my son, Taichi.

102
00:06:31,508 --> 00:06:34,318
I'm divorced and single right now.

103
00:06:34,488 --> 00:06:36,448
Nice to meet you, I'm Tajima Taichi.

104
00:06:36,448 --> 00:06:39,248
Thank you for being friends
with my mother.

105
00:06:40,128 --> 00:06:41,848
You have such a good kid.

106
00:06:41,848 --> 00:06:44,812
There's been a lot of times when I'm not around
because of work, so it just happened naturally.

107
00:06:45,178 --> 00:06:46,888
- And you come back home drunk, right?
- Hey now...

108
00:06:46,888 --> 00:06:50,108
- You promised not to say that...
- Here.

109
00:06:50,568 --> 00:06:52,628
Large serving of Vermicelli salad...

110
00:06:52,958 --> 00:06:55,938
This one's a special kid's meal.

111
00:06:56,038 --> 00:06:57,698
- Thank you.
- Thanks for waiting.

112
00:06:58,048 --> 00:06:59,948
We're digging in.

113
00:07:00,758 --> 00:07:03,008
Hot? Is it good?

114
00:07:03,718 --> 00:07:05,038
- I'm glad.
- Mm, good.

115
00:07:05,408 --> 00:07:06,868
Where's Sayuri-san today?

116
00:07:06,868 --> 00:07:09,238
She's been hospitalized for appendicitis.

117
00:07:09,728 --> 00:07:12,728
- Plus, today was the class reunion.
- Then, I feel sorry for her.

118
00:07:13,188 --> 00:07:15,718
So we went and paid her a visit today.

119
00:07:17,358 --> 00:07:19,148
Long time no see.

120
00:07:20,368 --> 00:07:21,978
Been a long time...

121
00:07:24,418 --> 00:07:27,658
Oh, dear. Pardon my appearance...

122
00:07:28,118 --> 00:07:30,658
What are you saying...
you're sick, of course!

123
00:07:30,658 --> 00:07:33,968
- Here, for you.
- Oh, thank you.

124
00:07:34,338 --> 00:07:36,448
Taichi-kun also came, huh.

125
00:07:36,448 --> 00:07:38,828
- Yes. This too is for you.
- What's this?

126
00:07:39,128 --> 00:07:41,898
It's your letter and music box
inside the time capsule.

127
00:07:44,028 --> 00:07:46,218
This brings back memories!

128
00:07:46,718 --> 00:07:48,978
Miho, do you remember this?

129
00:07:49,098 --> 00:07:52,578
I sure did! Hey, what's written in the letter?
Let me read it.

130
00:07:52,578 --> 00:07:54,708
No way! I will read it later by myself.

131
00:07:55,708 --> 00:07:56,708
How stingy.

132
00:07:56,758 --> 00:07:58,548
Even though we took pains to
bring it to her... right?

133
00:07:58,548 --> 00:08:01,248
She's right. Why don't you read
and let them hear it?

134
00:08:01,248 --> 00:08:03,798
Mom, not you too...

135
00:08:03,798 --> 00:08:05,838
Come, please replace these flowers.

136
00:08:05,838 --> 00:08:07,338
Sure, sure...

137
00:08:07,338 --> 00:08:08,638
Ma'am, I'll do it...

138
00:08:08,638 --> 00:08:11,178
No, no... you took time to come here so...

139
00:08:11,178 --> 00:08:12,388
Hey Sayuri.

140
00:08:12,388 --> 00:08:14,878
Shigacchi said he's still single.

141
00:08:15,098 --> 00:08:16,908
It's good news, right?

142
00:08:21,708 --> 00:08:24,418
Komatsu hasn't changed at all, huh?

143
00:08:24,418 --> 00:08:26,178
I was surprised.

144
00:08:26,518 --> 00:08:29,608
She's still the same old sweet Sayuri...

145
00:08:29,958 --> 00:08:32,008
Her dad died early on...

146
00:08:32,008 --> 00:08:34,608
...she and her mom had been
living together all this time so...

147
00:08:34,608 --> 00:08:37,428
It seems she can't leave
her mother on her own.

148
00:08:37,428 --> 00:08:40,618
Hmm... You know her pretty well huh.

149
00:08:40,918 --> 00:08:43,068
Since we've come a long way.

150
00:08:43,068 --> 00:08:45,958
Even when I was worried about
giving birth for the first time...

151
00:08:46,168 --> 00:08:48,548
When I was also depressed at the time
I decided to get a divorce...

152
00:08:48,548 --> 00:08:51,878
...it was Sayuri who always supported me.

153
00:08:52,328 --> 00:08:56,798
Well then, when Komatsu is discharged from
the hospital, let's have a celebration.

154
00:08:56,998 --> 00:08:59,458
- Let the three of us get together again.
- Yeah, let's do that.

155
00:08:59,708 --> 00:09:03,058
Master, make sure to prepare
lots of vermicelli salad, okay?

156
00:09:03,058 --> 00:09:04,558
Sure thing.

157
00:09:06,348 --> 00:09:08,458
Well, good night.
We enjoyed the food.

158
00:09:08,458 --> 00:09:10,618
- Are you all right?
- Yeah.

159
00:09:10,618 --> 00:09:13,318
Thanks, Master!

160
00:09:13,458 --> 00:09:16,438
- He's sleeping soundly.
- He is. Is he heavy?

161
00:09:16,438 --> 00:09:19,438
- No. I'm okay.
- Really? Thank you.

162
00:09:42,998 --> 00:09:45,868
- Congratulations on your discharge!
- Thank you.

163
00:09:45,868 --> 00:09:48,638
- Okay. Well then, let's toast.
- Here, thanks for waiting.

164
00:09:49,098 --> 00:09:51,578
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

165
00:09:52,328 --> 00:09:54,578
Congratulations. I'm happy for you.

166
00:09:54,578 --> 00:09:56,898
Thank you so much.

167
00:09:58,288 --> 00:10:00,598
But still I wasn't able
to go to the class reunion.

168
00:10:00,598 --> 00:10:02,648
After going through the trouble
of organizing it and yet...

169
00:10:02,818 --> 00:10:06,518
Stop complaining. Are you
dissatisfied with just me and Shigacchi?

170
00:10:06,518 --> 00:10:08,108
I'm not saying that...

171
00:10:08,108 --> 00:10:11,828
But I wondered if everyone else
is doing fine...

172
00:10:11,828 --> 00:10:15,098
Yeah... but 25 years have truly passed...

173
00:10:15,098 --> 00:10:19,798
Everyone has changed. Gotten married
and having families, especially the guys...

174
00:10:21,278 --> 00:10:24,068
Shiga-kun, you haven't changed at all.

175
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:26,138
Neither have you.

176
00:10:28,398 --> 00:10:31,008
But with Tajima...

177
00:10:31,008 --> 00:10:33,318
When I first saw you, I hardly recognized you.

178
00:10:33,318 --> 00:10:34,358
Hang on, what do you mean?

179
00:10:34,358 --> 00:10:38,088
- That I've become more like an Auntie?
- No, no. I'm not saying that...

180
00:10:38,088 --> 00:10:40,458
It's okay. 'Cause y'see,
your insides haven't changed.

181
00:10:40,458 --> 00:10:42,038
- Huh?
- What does that mean?

182
00:10:42,038 --> 00:10:44,518
You're scary when you get angry.

183
00:10:44,518 --> 00:10:46,128
That doesn't make me happy at all!

184
00:10:53,748 --> 00:10:56,508
Hey... He's a good guy, isn't he? Shigacchi.

185
00:10:57,298 --> 00:10:58,288
Yeah.

186
00:10:58,558 --> 00:11:00,108
Go and invite him out...

187
00:11:00,108 --> 00:11:02,148
I can't do such a thing so suddenly.

188
00:11:02,468 --> 00:11:05,698
- I just met him the other day.
- What are you saying...

189
00:11:05,698 --> 00:11:07,638
You met him 25 years ago.

190
00:11:07,638 --> 00:11:09,238
Yeah but it's...

191
00:11:09,238 --> 00:11:11,218
Oh, but it's okay 'cause
you're both single.

192
00:11:11,408 --> 00:11:12,708
Even you...

193
00:11:12,708 --> 00:11:17,178
For me, my son is enough.

194
00:11:17,178 --> 00:11:18,598
After all, my son's quite a looker, isn't he?

195
00:11:18,598 --> 00:11:21,198
He IS a cutie...

196
00:11:22,437 --> 00:11:24,938
Huh? What is it?
What are you guys talking about?

197
00:11:25,508 --> 00:11:27,118
Secret.

198
00:11:27,921 --> 00:11:30,438
Okay now. We've arrived.

199
00:11:30,828 --> 00:11:32,728
Put her down on the sofa.

200
00:11:32,728 --> 00:11:35,288
Okay now... Careful...

201
00:11:36,448 --> 00:11:39,378
We're here. Here you go.

202
00:11:39,378 --> 00:11:41,138
Ah~ goodness.

203
00:11:41,138 --> 00:11:43,098
It's been a long time...

204
00:11:43,098 --> 00:11:45,508
...since Miho has been this far gone.

205
00:11:45,988 --> 00:11:48,838
She was so glad when you got better.

206
00:11:49,218 --> 00:11:53,838
She said the other day, you have always
supported her when things were difficult.

207
00:11:56,998 --> 00:11:59,668
I was only by her side.

208
00:11:59,668 --> 00:12:02,308
Miho overcame her own problems herself...

209
00:12:02,541 --> 00:12:04,428
Because she's a strong person.

210
00:12:05,988 --> 00:12:08,608
Is it not perhaps that she has
unexpectedly become reliant on you?

211
00:12:08,608 --> 00:12:10,948
- What?
- It's gotta be, just look at her...

212
00:12:10,948 --> 00:12:13,578
...she can't sleep soundly at all.

213
00:12:15,708 --> 00:12:17,248
Can't be helped... indeed...

214
00:12:23,182 --> 00:12:25,866
Sensei, goodbye!

215
00:12:25,866 --> 00:12:29,076
Okay, goodbye.
Be careful on your way home.

216
00:12:29,076 --> 00:12:30,816
We will.

217
00:12:36,807 --> 00:12:43,116
(Note: She's humming "Wakare no Kyoku" or
"Song of Parting" = Chopin's "Étude Op. 10, No. 3")

218
00:12:43,266 --> 00:12:45,036
Sayuri-sensei.

219
00:13:04,626 --> 00:13:06,956
Sayuri-san, long time no see.

220
00:13:07,076 --> 00:13:08,796
Good evening.

221
00:13:09,086 --> 00:13:11,376
Welcome. Are you alone today?

222
00:13:11,976 --> 00:13:16,476
Yes. Bean vermicelli salad and beer please.

223
00:13:16,716 --> 00:13:17,966
Sure thing.

224
00:13:22,166 --> 00:13:26,536
I've heard...
you were hospitalized for appendicitis?

225
00:13:26,736 --> 00:13:28,976
Too bad about the reunion.

226
00:13:28,976 --> 00:13:30,066
Yeah...

227
00:13:30,066 --> 00:13:35,166
The other day... Miho-san brought her
son along and that classmate...

228
00:13:35,166 --> 00:13:37,396
...uh... Shigacchi?

229
00:13:37,396 --> 00:13:39,146
- The vermicelli salad guy?
- That's the one.

230
00:13:39,146 --> 00:13:41,946
I had mistaken him for Miho-san's husband...

231
00:13:41,946 --> 00:13:43,816
I was so embarrassed.

232
00:13:46,246 --> 00:13:50,716
That will... likely become true.

233
00:14:00,466 --> 00:14:02,816
Oh my gosh...

234
00:14:05,736 --> 00:14:11,396
Many things have changed
...but it still brings back memories.

235
00:14:11,596 --> 00:14:14,706
My seat was here.

236
00:14:17,516 --> 00:14:21,246
Mine was here.

237
00:14:23,576 --> 00:14:28,346
I remember it quite well...
Even though 25 years have passed.

238
00:14:30,086 --> 00:14:33,816
Shiga-kun's seat was over there.

239
00:14:34,166 --> 00:14:37,696
I was always watching
Shiga-kun from here.

240
00:14:38,736 --> 00:14:44,356
Us sitting here... reminds me of
many things from those days...

241
00:14:47,786 --> 00:14:51,046
Sayuri, I'm sorry.

242
00:14:51,716 --> 00:14:54,176
What's the matter? All of a sudden...

243
00:14:54,746 --> 00:14:58,916
Shiga-kun told me he loves me...

244
00:14:59,566 --> 00:15:00,936
What?

245
00:15:02,176 --> 00:15:06,516
He asked me to go out with him
with the premise of marriage.

246
00:15:07,696 --> 00:15:09,016
What do you mean...?

247
00:15:09,406 --> 00:15:13,606
At first, I rejected him because
I know how you feel about him.

248
00:15:14,856 --> 00:15:16,836
But you know...

249
00:15:17,006 --> 00:15:20,906
I've done some thinking...
about him, and Taichi too...

250
00:15:22,566 --> 00:15:26,636
When I take a look in the mirror,
and really face it...

251
00:15:26,636 --> 00:15:30,066
I think to myself,
"Ah... I like him, too."

252
00:15:30,066 --> 00:15:31,526
Enough! I don't want to hear it!

253
00:15:31,526 --> 00:15:33,216
Please listen, Sayuri...

254
00:15:33,216 --> 00:15:35,726
Don't say things as you please!

255
00:15:35,726 --> 00:15:37,296
I'm sorry.

256
00:15:38,036 --> 00:15:42,396
But... I don't want to lie
to my own feelings.

257
00:15:43,506 --> 00:15:48,756
Then...
what about my feelings!

258
00:15:48,756 --> 00:15:52,046
It's ALWAYS like this with you.

259
00:15:52,046 --> 00:15:54,396
When you come to talk to me,
you already have your answer.

260
00:15:54,396 --> 00:15:57,866
You just want to affirm yourself!

261
00:15:57,866 --> 00:16:00,306
Even at the time of your first marriage...

262
00:16:00,306 --> 00:16:02,786
I told you to think about it
carefully before marrying, right?

263
00:16:02,786 --> 00:16:04,896
And yet you had your own answer after all...

264
00:16:04,896 --> 00:16:08,386
I can't help it! I can't live
any other way than that.

265
00:16:08,386 --> 00:16:10,116
If that's the case...!

266
00:16:10,426 --> 00:16:12,916
...What do you need me for?

267
00:16:18,126 --> 00:16:22,236
I had been admiring you since the old days.

268
00:16:23,646 --> 00:16:25,776
You're able to pull yourself together...

269
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:28,266
Even if you fail, you're always positive...

270
00:16:28,266 --> 00:16:31,476
I thought it would be great
if I too become like you..

271
00:16:33,186 --> 00:16:35,456
But you know...

272
00:16:36,536 --> 00:16:39,336
I can not become strong like you.

273
00:16:46,486 --> 00:16:47,956
Thanks for waiting.

274
00:16:53,106 --> 00:16:56,306
The letter that I placed in the time capsule...

275
00:16:56,706 --> 00:16:59,226
I wrote, "I want to marry
the person I love..."

276
00:16:59,226 --> 00:17:03,326
"...and make him vermicelli salad."

277
00:17:05,086 --> 00:17:09,586
Can't believe I wrote such a thing...
I had completely forgotten about it.

278
00:17:11,356 --> 00:17:16,056
I also placed this music box along
with the letter but...

279
00:17:30,156 --> 00:17:33,156
Oh... It's "Song of Parting".

280
00:17:34,456 --> 00:17:37,966
Miho gave this to me for my birthday.

281
00:17:37,966 --> 00:17:40,566
Because I liked this song.

282
00:17:41,986 --> 00:17:44,826
It's the perfect song for me now.

283
00:17:45,066 --> 00:17:47,236
What a laugh, huh?

284
00:17:47,956 --> 00:17:51,986
That's right.
Please forget, and laugh about it.

285
00:17:53,296 --> 00:17:55,576
You're right!

286
00:17:56,556 --> 00:18:00,736
Okay! Today, I'm all about eating!

287
00:18:00,906 --> 00:18:02,806
I'm digging in.

288
00:18:14,006 --> 00:18:17,126
Master, the bean vermicelli salad...

289
00:18:17,126 --> 00:18:19,916
...is super delicious.

290
00:18:20,426 --> 00:18:22,226
Really.

291
00:18:23,216 --> 00:18:24,916
Thank you.

292
00:18:50,316 --> 00:18:52,376
It's okay...

293
00:18:53,126 --> 00:18:55,426
You don't have to force
yourself to laugh.

294
00:19:26,479 --> 00:19:32,586
<i>Perhaps tonight's rain is
the rain of Sayuri-san's tears.</i>

295
00:20:05,666 --> 00:20:07,606
Good morning.

296
00:20:09,896 --> 00:20:11,946
Good morning.

297
00:20:15,936 --> 00:20:17,906
I'm sorry about yesterday.

298
00:20:17,906 --> 00:20:20,726
I kind of cried like an idiot.

299
00:20:20,906 --> 00:20:22,726
It doesn't matter.

300
00:20:27,866 --> 00:20:33,506
I thought to bring this and to throw it away.

301
00:20:33,706 --> 00:20:35,506
You're gonna throw it?

302
00:21:01,536 --> 00:21:03,236
Hello...

303
00:21:06,126 --> 00:21:07,906
<i>"Miho..."</i>

304
00:21:10,976 --> 00:21:13,646
<i>"Be happy, okay?"</i>

305
00:21:16,956 --> 00:21:22,856
And... I'll be stronger.

306
00:21:25,516 --> 00:21:28,236
So...

307
00:21:29,086 --> 00:21:32,036
Be happy, okay?

308
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:34,796
Okay.

309
00:21:35,706 --> 00:21:37,756
Thank you.

310
00:21:50,252 --> 00:21:54,666
The season for harusame* is already finished.
(Again, double meaning for "spring rain"
and "vermicelli")

311
00:21:56,106 --> 00:21:58,256
Yeah.

312
00:22:04,008 --> 00:22:06,048
Well then...

313
00:22:18,346 --> 00:22:20,646
After boiling, wash the cellophane noodles
with running water...

314
00:22:20,646 --> 00:22:22,936
Drain it well.

315
00:22:22,936 --> 00:22:26,356
Add your choice of ingredients
like cucumber, ham and cloud ear mushrooms.

316
00:22:26,356 --> 00:22:29,326
To give the dressing a rich flavor,
add green onion oil.

317
00:22:29,326 --> 00:22:31,486
It will also add depth to the taste.

318
00:22:31,876 --> 00:22:34,026
- Thanks for waiting.
- Ah, here it is!

319
00:22:34,026 --> 00:22:36,686
Master, macaroni salad for me.

320
00:22:36,856 --> 00:22:38,326
Sure thing.

321
